fields.name: Camano Island Peru – Light Roast -450g
fields.description: One of the highest in elevation in the region, this Peru bean has sweet, fruity tones that lend towards a naturally sweet cup. Our Organic Peru Coffee is our lightest bodied coffee which makes it a great choice for the coffee drinker that enjoys drinking lots of coffee yet doesn’t want to sacrifice in the flavor of the cup. This coffee is great anytime of the day and compliments many meals.

fields.name: Crafted Peru Light Roast - 450g
fields.description: This peruvian roast exemplifies the consistency and balance of coffee from this region. With a smooth, full body (no bitterness), our perfectly peruvian batches take “drinkability” to a whole new level.

fields.name: ALVARI Peru Amazonas Coffee - 500g
fields.description: This Peruvian Arabica offers heavy sweetness, fruit like cherry, apricot to chocolate flavors with an excellent balance.

fields.name: Grounds & Hounds Peruvian Light Roast Decaf - 350g
fields.description: For the light roast decaf lover, our Single Origin Peruvian Decaf coffee uses the highest quality 100% Arabica, 100% Fair Trade Organic Peruvian beans that can be found, which are then decaffeinated through Swiss Water Processing. Featuring notes of toasted vanilla, red apple and low acidity, this decaf is a must try!

fields.name: My Vegan Organic Raw Cacao Powder -250 gr
fields.description: Made from 100% organic raw cacao beans, this finely ground powder is a natural source of all three macronutrients — protein, carbs, and fat — along with the essential minerals, potassium, magnesium, iron, copper and manganese. The result? A rich-tasting powder that’s a great addition to your daily diet.

fields.name: Zint Raw Organic Cacao Powder - 905g
fields.description: Dark, decadent, romantic. Chocolate is one of nature’s singular pleasures. And while most store-bought chocolate comes with added ingredients that undermine the health benefits, chocolate in the form of pure cacao powder is nothing short of a delicious anti-aging superfood. With 20 times the antioxidant content of blueberries, it’s one of densest antioxidants in the world. It’s also packed with resveratrol, magnesium, iron, manganese and mood-enhancing compounds, offering profound benefits for your happiness, beauty, heart health and overall wellbeing.

fields.name: SuperFood World Organic Peruvian Raw Cacao - Premium Cocoa Powder 500g
fields.description: GUILT FREE HEALTHY CHOCOLATE INDULGENCE – Our Premium Organic Cacao Powder offers a rich natural chocolate flavour without the unwanted sugars and chemicals found in processed chocolate. Packed full of antioxidants you can bake healthy, delicious brownies, cookies, chocolate cakes or make a delicious warming hot chocolate. HIGHLY PRIZED PERUVIAN CRIOLLO BEANS – Superfood World Premium Organic Cacao Powder is derived from prized Criollo Cacao Beans, which are regarded as the highest quality variations of cacao, offering an exquisite natural chocolate taste.

fields.name: Natierra,Organic Cacao Powder, (225 g)
fields.description: Our journey starts in the Cacao orchards of Peru… Local Farmers grow delicious heirloom cacao pods. The Criollo Bean is a rare and flavorful type of cacao. The Beans are harvested, fermented, dried, and ground. Try some in morning smoothies and favorite baking recipes!

fields.name: Viva Naturals Certified Organic Cacao Powder
fields.description: UPLIFTS MOOD AND ELEVATES ENERGY - add cacao to your favorite cup of java for a morning pick-me-up and an immediate boost of energy. Transform ordinary smoothies and shakes into chocolate wonder with heavenly cacao.

fields.name: Naturale Bio Organic Cacao Powder - 250g
fields.description: ORIGIN OF CACAO: Cacao is what Linnaeus named Theobroma, or ‘Food of the Gods’, from the Greek ‘theos’ meaning ‘god’ and ‘broma’ meaning ‘food’. The cacao plant is a tropical tree whose natural habitat is the lowest layer of the rain forest. Its favourable habitat is therefore the tropical rain forest, which has a more or less constant climate throughout the year, with abundant and regular rainfall.

fields.name: Moreish - Peruvian Organic Fairtrade - Single Origin Coffee Beans - 1kg
fields.description: Fruity, floral and sweet flavour notes - with subtle hints of Caramel. Fairtrade accredited and Organic certified. Each bag contains 100% Arabica coffee beans that are ethically and sustainably sourced. Medium roasted to perfection. Grown on the sloping mountainous areas of San Ignacio, Carjamaca, Peru

fields.name: Volcanica Peru Coffee, Organic - 450g
fields.description: The Peru Coffee is also known as Tres Cumbres and is organically grown in the Chanchamayo region at the highest ranges of the South American Andes and the Amazon River basin. The Peruvian coffee produces a complex, full-bodied coffee with floral, smoky overtones, a bright aromatic finish, a gentle acidity, and a clean, bright aromatic finish.

fields.name: Cooper’s Cask Peruvian - 450 g
fields.description: ORGANIC COLD BREW COFFEE PERUVIAN RESERVE - COARSELY GROUND - Medium Roast - by the Master Roasters at Cooper's Cask Coffee. We use an organic coffee bean profiled to a medium roast level. Cooper's is a USDA Certified Coffee Roaster!

fields.name: AmazonFresh Organic Fair Trade Peru Ground Coffee, Medium Roast - 350g
fields.description: Fragrant medium roast Peruvian coffee with a smooth finish. 100% Arabica coffee grown in Peru. Fair Trade certified, USDA Organic coffee.

fields.name: Coffee Bean Direct French Roast Peru, Whole Bean Coffee - 500g
fields.description: Coffee is roasted fresh immediately prior to packaging and shipping from coffee bean direct's facility. Coffee beans are slow-roasted to bring out a fuller, more even flavor. Great for personal use. Ideal for chefs and food service.

fields.name: Cubico Coffee Peru Coffee - Freshly Roasted Coffee - 450g
fields.description: Freshly Roasted Peruvian Beans - Cubico Coffees are roasted in small batches and our roasters sign and date each bag to ensure freshness.

fields.name: LAIRD SUPERFOOD Organic Medium Roast Peruvian Whole Bean Coffee - 350g
fields.description: FAIR TRADE ORGANIC COFFEE - Laird's Coffee Arabica beans are organically grown at high altitudes. We think you'll agree that they produce incredibly complex flavors that yield phenomenal tasting coffee.

fields.name: Equal Exchange Organic Peruvian Medium Roast Coffee -1kg
fields.description: Sweet, floral and juicy with sparkling white grape, a soft mouthfeel and prolonged cocoa in the finish.

fields.name: Java Planet Single-Origin Medium Dark Roast - 450g
fields.description: A medium-dark roasted decaf with notes of chocolate and a smooth body. Swiss water process decaffeinated.

fields.name: OHM Coffe Roasters Medium Full Roast, Peruvian Whole Bean Coffee - 350
fields.description: Flavors of blackberry, clove, and leather. Inspired by the Full Stack flavor profile but without the caffeine, this water process decaf prefers nightclubs over stadiums. Current blend: - 100% Peru Fair Trade Organic, Swiss Water.

fields.name: Arcaffé Peru FTO - 500g
fields.description: Arcaffé Peru Fair Trade Organic coffee beans are grown in remote areas of Peru, marked with the Fairtrade certification and CSC. It is a coffee with a full body, soft acidity and unusual notes of honey and roasted almonds. The flavor is topped with a mild flavor of cocoa. The coffee is grown by small producers. The shrubs are protected in the shade of native forest. The entire processing cycle of coffee takes place at the harvest, at 1200 - 1800 m. The 100% Arabica beans are washed and then dried.

fields.name: Coffee Masters Peruvian Coffee Beans - 1kg
fields.description: 100% Organic Arabica Coffee Beans, Soft and Well-Balanced - Coffee Masters Peruvian Coffee Beans are soft and well balanced with a gentle, citrus-like acidity, which is complimented by a delicate sweetness and smooth, silky body.

fields.name: Organic Ground Peru Coffee - 250g
fields.description: Alternative Peru Organic Ground Coffee 3 is a very balanced coffee with a smooth aroma. A full-bodied and balanced coffee. Low acidity and intense flavor. With a pleasant aroma of cocoa and fresh grass and a subtle floral memory.

fields.name: Dark 77 % Peru Chocolate Table t - 125
fields.description: Organic dark chocolate made with criollo cocoa from Peru.

fields.name: Cacaosuyo Cuzo, 80% Perú - 150g
fields.description: Cacaosuyo is a tree to bar Peruvian chocolate maker with 100% traceability. They pay careful attention to the cacao they use at all stages from harvest, fermentation to the processing of cacao to make the best possible chocolate. Cacaosuyo is so particular about their beans to ensure the best quality that their beans are brought to dedicated labs for analysis.

fields.name: Orquidea Dark Chocolate with Quinoa - 80g
fields.description: Ingredientes: Organic cacao liquor, organic cacao butter, organic sugar, organic quinoa and soy lecithin.

fields.name: Chocosombra 70% Pure Peruvian Chocolate Bar - 35g
fields.description: Grown in the Peruvian cloud forest under a canopy of native trees our cacao beans embody the flavors of the nutrient dense soil in which they are grown. The 70% is our most popular bar and great entry into dark chocolate. Our cacao beans are imported directly from a single estate family owned farm. This farm practices bio-dynamic farming; this is a system that integrates the highest level of sustainability practices for the land and humanitarian practices for labor. Our chocolate is slavery free.

fields.name: Peru Inambari FTO Very Dark Roast - 250g
fields.description: This Fairtrade Organic Peruvian coffee is grown by farmers from the Agraria Frontera San Ignacio Cooperative. The farm lies in the Caijamarca region in the district of Coipa. Most of the coffee cherries were picked in August when they were at their optimum level of maturation and sweetness. The farms are found within a group of protected areas where many wild animals such as spectacled bears and jaguars roam.

fields.name: Warrior Coffee Peru Dark Coffee Beans - 250g
fields.description: Good coffee is like magic. The clear and delicious Warrior Coffee Peru is (dark) roasted to perfection from handpicked, organic certified coffee berries. Its silky smooth taste is embedded with sensual savours of chocolate and nut – all contributing to an experience of purest possible enjoyment. Choosing organic coffee from an artisan roastery ensures the cleanest, most delicious taste every time. Consider yourself warned though, once you go good there’s no turning bad.

fields.name: Paramaunt Coffee Fair Trade Organic Peru Dark Roast - 850g
fields.description: Fair Trade Certified, USDA 100% Organic Certified. Medium body, slightly sweet with a mild acidity. Purchasing Fair Trade is supporting coffee growers around the world to receive fair market value for their crops,This coffee is 100% organic  - good for you...good for the environment.

fields.name: LAIRD SUPERFOOD Organic Medium Roast Peruvian Whole Bean Coffee - 350g
fields.description: Laird Superfood Peruvian Ethically Sourced Dark Roast Ground Coffee is one of the top-rated premium coffee beans in the world. Peruvian Organic Dark Roast Coffee.

fields.name: Café Altura Organic Peruvian Coffee - 450g
fields.description: Dark roasted flavorful and aromatic coffee.  Delicious iced or hot. Perfect way to start your morning. Great for a quick treat or pick-me-up any time of day or night. Organic.
